## You are free to

- **Share** — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format for any
  purpose, even commercially
- **Adapt** — remix, transform, and build upon the material for any purpose, even
  commercially

## Under the following terms

- **Attribution** — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the license,
  and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in any reasonable manner, but not
  in any way that suggests the licensor endorses you or your use.

- **No additional restrictions** — You may not apply legal terms or technological
  measures that legally restrict others from doing anything the license permits.

## What This Means

**For the standard and methodology (this repository):**

- You may use, share, and adapt OPENSPEC.md, the writing guide, issue templates,
  and all documentation freely
- Attribution to "Open Specification" is appreciated but the standard is designed
  to be adopted widely

**For specifications you write:**

- You own your specifications completely
- You choose your own license (CC BY 4.0, CC BY-SA 4.0, proprietary, etc.)

**For implementations built from specifications:**

- You own your code completely
- Implementations are not derivative works of the specification or this standard
- You may license your implementation however you choose (MIT, GPL, proprietary, etc.)

